---
// src/pages/crazy-8s.astro
// Fully validated, premium web text rules console block layout
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>01 Soloverse - Crazy 8's Official Rulebook</title>
    <style>
        /* 1. ARCHITECTURE THEME MAPS */
        :root {
            --bg-main: #0f1015;
            --bg-card: #171922;
            --text-primary: #ffffff;
            --text-secondary: #f3f4f6;
            --text-muted: #9ca3af;
            --text-divider: #2d313f;
            --color-accent: #3b82f6; /* Classic Blue */
        }

        :root[data-theme="light"] {
            --bg-main: #f4f5f7;
            --bg-card: #ffffff;
            --text-primary: #111216;
            --text-secondary: #1f2937;
            --text-muted: #4b5563;
            --text-divider: #d1d5db;
            --color-accent: #1d4ed8; /* Darker Blue for high text contrast */
        }

        body {
            font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
            background: var(--bg-main);
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            max-width: 750px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            line-height: 1.7;
            transition: background 0.3s, color 0.3s;
        }
        .back-link {
            display: inline-block;
            color: var(--color-accent);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            transition: color 0.15s;
        }
        .back-link:hover { color: var(--text-primary); }
        h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 5px; font-weight: 800; }
        .version-tag { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 40px; font-weight: 600; }
        
        /* Table of Contents Styling Layout */
        .toc-box { 
            background: var(--bg-card); 
            border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); 
            padding: 24px; 
            border-radius: 12px; 
            margin: 30px 0; 
        }
        .toc-title { margin: 0 0 15px 0; color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; }
        .toc-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
        .toc-link { color: var(--text-muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; transition: color 0.15s; }
        .toc-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

        /* Rulebook Section Content Blocks */
        h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; color: #0000ff; margin-top: 50px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-bottom: 8px; font-weight: 700; }
        p { color: var(--text-secondary); margin: 16px 0; }
        
        /* Card Reference Data Lists */
        .card-list { background: var(--bg-card); border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-left: 4px solid var(--text-divider); }
        .card-item { margin: 10px 0; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); }
        .card-name { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 700; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <a href="/" class="back-link">📂 Return to Shelf Deck</a>

    <h1>01 Soloverse - Crazy 8's</h1>
    <div class="version-tag">Game Rulebook Component v13.0.0</div>

    <!-- UNIVERSAL TABLE OF CONTENTS: Snaps instantly on PC, iPad, and Android Opera GX! -->
    <div class="toc-box">
        <div class="toc-title">📋 Index Jump Matrix</div>
        <ul class="toc-list">
            <li><a href="#section1" class="toc-link">1. Component Setup Layout</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section2" class="toc-link">2. Core Gameplay Parameters</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section3" class="toc-link">3. Chaos Card Index Reference</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- SECTION 1 CONTENT -->
    <h2 id="section1">1. Component Setup Layout</h2>
    <p>Shuffle the custom Soloverse tracking matrix thoroughly. Deal exactly seven card profiles straight to each active solo user seat position. Place the remaining deck framework facedown in the center grid zone to instantiate the draw stack layer...</p>

    <!-- SECTION 2 CONTENT -->
    <h2 id="section2">2. Core Gameplay Parameters</h2>
    <p>On your active tactical turn phase sequence, matching the active rank digit or core color profile of the current top discard layout element is mandatory. If a user profile cannot deploy a matching item asset, drawing a single tracking block from the central stack layer is automatically enforced...</p>

    <!-- SECTION 3 CONTENT -->
    <h2 id="section3">3. Chaos Card Index Reference</h2>
    <p>Deploying modifier assets alters standard system operation. Review the core functionality traits below:</p>
    <div class="card-list">
        <div class="card-item"><span class="card-name">♦️ Skip Card:</span> Bypasses the immediate next user seat framework entirely.</div>
        <div class="card-item"><span class="card-name">♣️ Reverse Card:</span> Inverts the directional orientation sequence of active turns.</div>
        <div class="card-item"><span class="card-name">♥️ Draw Two Card:</span> Forces the target node matrix to pull two cards and freeze their turn layout.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Quietly checks the device storage to match the bookshelf theme choice instantly -->
    <script is:inline>
        const activeTheme = localStorage.getItem('soloverse-theme') || 'dark';
        document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', activeTheme);
    </script>

</body>
</html>
